< Text>
DELICIOUS. Love the varieties and the fact that you can pick small or large sizes. Their sausage pasties are excellent, as are the turkey. The crust is flaky, buttery deliciousness and complements the fillings perfectly. Do yourself a favor and save room for an apple dessert pasties. Prices are very reasonable. Just an FYI, they are cash only!< /Text>

<Text>The pasties are delicious and well worth $5.95 for a regular size pastie. Perfect amount of food for lunch at this price. My husband will order 2 on a hungry day because he eats more but will only get half way through the second unless he's really hungry.
The only downfall is they are reheated which makes the crust a little less flakey when using a microwave but if you reheat at home in the oven or half microwave and half toaster oven, it turns out more flakey and delicious!<//Text>< pictures>

<text>I really wanted to love this place, because I drove a 1/2 an hour to get here. I love pasties.  I just didn't love these pasties. I grew up loving them, and that's one of the reasons I wanted to love these. I've been looking for a great place to find great pasties, and so far, no success.
There was a lot of meat and a lot of potatoes inside and the crust was palatable.  The problem was that they are just too dry. You should be able to just pick them up and eat them maybe have something to drink with them, but not necessarily. With these pasties,  You must slather than in gravy, have something to drink, ladel them with butter, or something.  They are just so very dry!
After hearing about this place and having wanted so very much to love them, I was so very disappointed that they weren't great as I had heard. I will keep looking for a really good pastie place.</text>< Pictures>

<review>Quaint little shop with the best Pasties in Grass Valley!</review>< pictures>

<UserId.>108592696243378374083< /UserId.><Name>Tiffany K</Name><date>1373053455830< /date><rate>3<//rate>< text>
CASH ONLY. Small shop off one of the side streets in downtown Grass Valley. Came here because I thought I'd try something different and because of all the reviews.

Pasties are pastry-covered, little "pies" that are normally savory, but they offer an apple one here. Known as the national dish of Cornwall in the UK, they were popular in this neck of the woods as miners from Cornwall came out here to try out their gold finding luck. Pronounced "pa-stee" as opposed to "pay-stee" -- those little things that strippers are found of. (But to be fair, a stripper could be partial to both.)

You can order pasties in a smaller size or regular. I recommend the regular, if you're kind of hungry. If you are really hungry, you might need two! The price for a regular size averaged about $4.95 or so.

They had choices of beef, chicken, vegetable, broccoli and cheese, apple, and I know I must have missed a couple of other ones. My daughter, being vegetarian, ordered the vegetable one and she could taste a distinct fridge flavor, so she wasn't too thrilled about that. I had the beef - the meat portion seemed more like broken up beef sausage, not mincemeat or steak cubes.

I ordered an apple one to try at home. They packed it with some icing that was delicious! Although the pasty itself had fridge flavor to it. I was advised to heat up in the microwave, but I stuck it in the oven as I wanted my pastry on the flakier side.

The seating area is tiny! So you may not be able to score a place to sit down. I noticed that they probably do a brisk business with catering orders, etc. as they sell cocktail pasties, a dozen for $14. I'd come back to get some of those if I was having a gathering!< /text>

This is a very good place for dining and for take out. Starts with great pizza. Very authentic New York style pizza. They also have great pasta dishes and good sandwiches. After jojo's closed down we needed to find a new restaurant pizza. It's just ok. Maybe marginally better than the high volume big chain pizza places. The crust was on the thin side for my liking and was a bit chewy, like it had been worked too long and the gluten over developed. I think hight top pizzas from Blaze will be our new local pizza of choice.< /Text>

<UserId.>103308427360857520520<//UserId.><name>Sharon Douglas</name><Time>1560779888050< /Time><Rating>5</Rating>< Text>
Located in the Stater's shopping center on Limonite. We puled up in front & could smell th garlic when we got out of the car & knew this was going to be good food. Looks like a little mom & pop pizza place but delivers high end Italian flavors. They serve everything from Pizza (up to 28-inch) to Subs... Great pasta dishes.. Spaghetti, manicotti, lasagna & more. The lasagna is our favorite.. they use real Mozzarella & ricotta cheeses. They also have many different salads to choose from. Graziano's has a Calzone that is bigger than the plate. The place is clean (a-rating). Staff very friendly & efficient. The prices are reasonable for the portion sizes & they have a lunch special for 5.95 with many items to choose from. In all a great little place for a nice meal.</Text>

This is a super cute small business that we should be supporting! The owner is very nice and you can tell he wants to ensure the quality of his products and his service.

We got the matcha latte with whipped cream, mocha with whipped cream, salmon cream cheese on a jalapeno cheddar bagel, and a bacon pepper jack breakfast on sesame bagel. All of it was so good!!

Executive Summary:
If I could give this business a 'zero' rating, I would.  One star is too much.  Don't waste your time and find another Triumph Service location.

Details:
Scheduled the break-in service for my Triumph with this place thinking they would be a good place to establish a Service relationship for the future of my motorcycle ownership; bad move!
The Service Rep Chris (spelling?) was rude, condescending, and disrespectful.   He didn't get up from his chair or bother to look me in the eye while I arrived at the Service area.  Which, by the way is tucked in the back, like you're going into someone's backyard...
Anyway, as he proceeded to ask his questions, he was giving out the feeling that he was bothered by my presence and couldn't wait to get me out of there. His demeanor was so rude and condescending that I asked if he had something against me or a problem with me bringing my bike for service.  Obviously, he says no...

I decided to go somewhere else, asked for my keys and left; that was the best decision, other than buying a Triumph, to-date!

Rick took the lead as i was internet lead, and answered every question i asked and he knew the programs off the top of his head (one dealer i went to didn't even know they had low interest finance or that extras were included in the sale from the manufacturer!)  Every time i sent an email i got one back no matter how little the question was. No one ever told me they would need me to set up a "VIP Appointment" to get the best deal!!!!  lol!!!

Pricing?  They won't get beat, but to be honest, they had great pricing out of the gate, and no need to haggle.   Very fair!  Better than fair probably.

After the sale i wanted to add accessories, and without having to ask i was offered a discount on anything i wanted!   Andy in PARTS was great. Knows his stuff, and told me he would ship my parts to me because i am not local.  Called back in later and spoke to him again and same great service!  OH!  And they have tons of selection!  Anything you need they have it!  I'm lucky my wife was with me or i would have shopped and picked up more great accessories!  Helmets gloves jackets and anything else you can think of.  A little place that's bigger inside than you may think.

Kevin the Finance guy was so quick and really painless.  Even my wife was surprised at how fast he got us through the process.

What can i say?  I wish i lived closer because the Service dept has a great rep as well.  I may even take a trip for service, just because if they do that half as well as the sales end i'll be happy!

Great place to do business.  Highly recommend!<//Review><Time>1530731650500<//Time>< user>

<Gmap_id>0x80e8291e4f851455:0xe00b4bcfdbb69d73<//Gmap_id>< Text>
SVC is by far the worst motorcycle dealer in Ventura County, if not all of Southern California.  Their parts department does not carry a large inventory insuring that their customers will have to wait.  Their service department is staffed by young, untrained technicians who perform shoddy work.

I purchased a motorcycle from them in 2001.  Two years later it developed an intermittent missing problem and I brought it to them under warranty.  They tried on three separate occasions to find and repair the problem and couldn't.  They ended up giving the bike back to me un-repaired.  I then brought the bike to a competing dealer who diagnosed and located the problem in 10 minutes, ordered the part and returned my motorcycle in three days.

While SVC had my motorcycle the last time under warranty, they kept it for 4 weeks, broke my carburetor float bowls, glued them back together with epoxy, replaced defective parts with used ones, stored it outside in the rain (customary for them) and they returned the motorcycle to me completely filthy and corroded.  They refused to repair the damage they had caused or even detail the bike.

I highly recommend that you avoid Simi Valley Cycles.</Text>

< review>
Food is ok but overpriced even by Truckee standards. Have been there many times and pizza is inconsistant. Servers are friendly and quick - there's usually only one person waiting/bartending and another cooking.

Don't bother to go for their Trivia Night promo. It's rigged as a group of employees wins 9 times out of 10. We've even heard them discussing the answers an hour before the game starts. And Tahoe Donner management is on record as supporting them.

If you want better pizza and fair trivia, try Best Pies Pizza a few miles away.< /review>

< Rating>

< Review>
100% a very poor and disapointing experience. I will not be eating at BJs again.

After our initial mothersday plans fell through we thought we could still have a decent dinner by having BJ's delivered so I ordered online from the BJs website.

At the time that the food was supposed to have already been delivered the delivery driver texted me to let me know he was at the BJs but our food wasn't ready (see attached photo).

The food eventually showed up 30 minutes late but the main course (the pizza we ordered) wasn't there so we were left with salad and desert for dinner.

When I called to figure out what the problem was I was put on hold for 10 minutes waiting for a manager. He was initially somewhat apologetic but quickly tried ot shift the blame to the delivery driver. He did offer to give me a gift card for the same value of my pizza but when I insisted on getting the amount refunded to my card instead (because I have no plans of going back to BJs) he acknowledged my request and then hung up on me before I could get confirmation or ask for the delivery fee and tip to be refunded (basically another $20 wasted on this dinner that we never recieved).

I understand that things slip through the cracks and people make mistakes, but the way this was handled after the fact was the worst. Order online at your own risk.</Review>

Free parking lot
Not too crowded or loud
Friendly staff
Despite great menu variety, sub par food and drink*
I would like to mention however, that we arrived about 45 (maybe up to 35) minutes prior to closing time and therefore intended to order our food Togo and were prepared to wait however long (no rush and our apologies to the staff ('cause we've been there, done that, and are now "one of those" on this particular night)); so after placing our order, we waited at the bar.

Anytime I've been to any other BJ's, they've had a "Strawberry Fields" martini (or something to that affect) on the menu and its the tops. Upon seeing this menu was sans my "go to" drink option, I inquired at the bartender who assured me that he knew of the drink and that it would be no problem to make it...
Worst drink ever (@ BJ's anyway). Passed it off (somehow) to my friend who just figured she'd down it mixed with her delicious tropical drink which, hey, thats her call (destroyed her drink but totally her fault). Anyway, we get our order and peace out just before (if not at) closing time.

We get home to find our food a mixed variety of either burnt or mushy...

No, we didn't call because: a. they were closed anyway b. we were just taking care of a personal matter that day/night with plans to head back home that next morning and c. mainly, we didn't want to deal with the stress that usually comes with "complaining" etc. etc.

*So this review is related to this particular BJ's on that particular night with those being the specifics potentially being the change and hopefully not the constant. But I'll let you be the judge. I will say, always, no matter what/where, I feel the majority of their menu is over priced; yet I still somehow end up returning at some point in life anyway. That's all :p<//Text>

When I took the top bun off the sandwich the bun was twice the size of the meat (Literally). I was surprised they would even serve this to anyone, it was basically a bread sandwich. I immediately told the server, (who looked embarrassed). I ordered a hamburger and fries. The hamburger was good,  But the service was horrible. The server never came back to the table to check on us. I had to flag down a different waiter for another iced tea. The other people in my party never received a refill or checked on about their food or drinks.</Text>

<name>FrankandJudy Yturralde< /name><Date>1425701336945</Date><Rate>3< /Rate>< Review>
We arrived at 3:30pm for a late lunch. As we walked thuogh the door, the music was so loud that we
almost turned around and walked out. We asked to be seated in the quietest corner of the restaurant
even though we were seated next to the kitchen door, it was a pleasant booth. We called earlier to
make sure that lunch would be served when we came in. We were told after being put on hold, that
lunch would be served no matter what time we came in. We ordered the unlimited soup and salad,
chicken quesdillas to start. Both were delicous. The chicken quesdilla only had 4 small pieces. It
should have had 4 more pieces. We then ordered the chicken tacos. They were delicous but very messyand too doughy.Even though we were very happy with the food, the waiter made a mistake and charged us the dinner price of $9.50 instead of the lunch price of $6.50. When I brought it to his attention, he informed me that he did not know that we had ordered off the lunch menu. He should have offered to correct the bill. What had happened was that a shift change happened in the middle of the meal, but since he didn't, we still paid the bill and left him 30% tip. Overall, the place was loud and extremely cold. The service has approved 100% since the last time we were there. We stopped going to our local BJ's because the service was so bad and managers were so indifferent to our
complaints about the service. That is why we only gave it 3 stars instead of 4 stars. We will definitely go back.      Judy&Frank</Review>
